quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  8,45,"Believers! When you encounter a party, remain firm and remember God much, so that you may succeed"
  8,46,"Obey God and His Messenger, and avoid dissension, lest you falter and are no longer held in awe. Have patience: God is with those who are patient"
  8,47,"Do not be like those who left their homes full of conceit and showing off to others. They debar others from the path of God: but God has knowledge of all their actions"
  8,48,"Satan made their deeds seem fair to them and said, \"None of the people shall prevail against you this day; I shall be your protector!\" But when the two forces came in sight of each other, he turned on his heels, saying, \"This is where I leave you: I see what you do not, and I fear God -- God is severe in His punishment"